    type: "evento",
    title: "QUERICO Tokyo x Fünk: Kyle Hall + Carlos Valdes + Hanzo Tono + Camila Valero & DJ Milka",
    subtitle: "Fünk · Mexico City",
    excerpt: "MAYO - JUEVE 07 QUERICO x FÜNK presenta: KYLE HALL HANZO TONO b2b CARLOS VALDES DJ MILKA b2b CAMILA VALERO We’re back to our favourite City and the best club in town– FÜNK, presenting: KYKE HALL, straight from Detroit, he is an electronic music producer and DJ known for his warm, soulful sound and intricate rhythms. Emerging in the late 2000s, he gained recognition for blending Detroit techno and house with influences from jazz, funk, and hip-hop. He has released music on labels such as Hyperdub, Apron, and his own imprints, Wild Oats & Forget The Clock. Hall remains a pioneer in Detroit’s underground dance music scene. CARLOS VALDES is a key figure in Amsterdam nightlife and a respected DJ, promoter, label owner, and co-founder of Isburning. For over two decades, he has played an important role in shaping the city’s electronic music and LGBTQIA+ club scene. He is known for his deep knowledge of house and techno, a vast vinyl collect with performances at renowned names like: Panorama Bar, Bassiani, Glastonbury, and Dekmantel Selectors. HANZO TONO is a multidisciplinary artist, producer & selector with over 20y across house, balearic, disco, synthwave and minimal sounds. He has performed at venues like Sisyphos, Kater Blau, Silencio, Razzmatazz, VENT & WOMB. Collaborated with brands like Jean Paul Gaultier & Hugo Boss. Resident of QUERICO and founder of his own label Mambo Diablo Records! DJ MILKA she is a producer, DJ and founder of @milkybaberecords, supporting women in electronic music. Also co-founder of Boyanza and vocalist/songwriter of Self Sabotage. Her sets fuse house, breaks, electro, and disco with fresh energy. Recently released Bitch Boss and is developing her hybrid live set. CAMILA VALERO is a DJ and producer from Mexico City known for her eclectic sound and vibrant energy. She has played major clubs and festivals including FÜNK, LooLoo, EDC Mexico, Trópico, and Corona Capital, with growing presence in New York and London. Her style blends deep house, UK garage, drum & bass, and hard groove. *Limited Early bird tickets out now : 200$",
